---
import LegalPageLayout from '../../layouts/LegalPageLayout.astro';
import { dataRequestPath } from '../../i18n/paths';
---

<LegalPageLayout
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="Faktum AI privacy policy and subscriber registry processing information."
  path="/en/privacy/"
>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-05-24 · version 2026-05-24-v2</p>

  <h2>Controller</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>PLACEHOLDER_TODO_CONTROLLER_NAME</strong><br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:marko@faktum-ai.com">marko@faktum-ai.com</a><br />
    Website: <a href="https://www.faktum-ai.com">www.faktum-ai.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Purposes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Sending the Faktum AI newsletter (once a week)</li>
    <li>Managing subscriber profiles (role, interests, language)</li>
    <li>Double opt-in confirmation and subscription management</li>
    <li>Fulfilling data subject rights (export, deletion)</li>
    <li>Aggregated audience statistics for sponsorship (no personal sales)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal bases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Newsletter:</strong> consent (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a))</li>
    <li><strong>Transactional emails:</strong> service delivery</li>
    <li><strong>Consent audit log:</strong> legitimate interest / compliance evidence</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data collected</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>Language preference (fi / en / both)</li>
    <li>Optional role and interest selections</li>
    <li>Signup source URL</li>
    <li>Consent version and timestamp</li>
    <li>Technical audit metadata (hashed IP, truncated user agent)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Active subscribers: until unsubscribe</li>
    <li>Inactive / unsubscribed: recommended 24–36 months for audit (TODO: confirm)</li>
    <li>After deletion request: personal data removed or anonymised; minimal legal log retained</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Processors</h2>
  <p>
    We process subscriber data as the controller. To run the technical service, we use the
    <strong>processors</strong> listed below — we do not sell, rent, or share the subscriber list with
    third parties for marketing. Processors act only on behalf of Faktum AI under contract.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>We do not store subscriber data on GitHub.</strong> GitHub is used for website source
    code version control only.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Cloudflare, Inc. — hosting, D1 subscriber registry (EU), KV, Pages Functions</li>
    <li>Resend, Inc. — confirmation and management emails (EU region, Ireland)</li>
    <li>Possible future ESP (Buttondown / MailerLite) — downstream copy only</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data location</h2>
  <p>
    The subscriber registry is stored in a Cloudflare D1 database in the EU. Email service Resend is
    configured for the EU region (Ireland). We do not transfer subscriber data abroad for marketing
    purposes. If a technical provider is based in the United States, processing relies on the
    provider’s DPA and, where required, standard contractual clauses (SCC).
  </p>

  <h2>Unsubscribing</h2>
  <p>
    You can unsubscribe at any time on our
    <a href="/en/subscribe/unsubscribe/">unsubscribe page</a>. Confirmation requires a personal link
    from your email — this prevents others from cancelling your subscription.
  </p>
  <p>
    The easiest way: open the <strong>Unsubscribe</strong> link in your latest newsletter or welcome
    email — it opens the unsubscribe page ready to confirm. If you cannot find the message, check
    your spam folder. You can also contact
    <a href="mailto:marko@faktum-ai.com">marko@faktum-ai.com</a> for help.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>You may access, rectify, erase, port, and withdraw consent for your data.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Data requests: <a href={dataRequestPath('en')}>your data page</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Privacy enquiries: <a href="mailto:marko@faktum-ai.com">marko@faktum-ai.com</a></p>
</LegalPageLayout>
